From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yocto Builder <builder@yoctoproject.org>
Date: Tue, 7 Jan 2026 03:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] DISABLE tegra194 driver for nvidia,tegra264-pcie

Thor (Tegra264) uses SBSA/ECAM PCIe controllers with different memory
regions (xal, xtl, xpl, ecam) than standard Tegra (dbi, appl, atu_dma).

The device tree should use "snps,dw-pcie-ecam" instead, which will
be handled by the generic DesignWare ECAM driver (pci-host-generic.c).

This patch removes nvidia,tegra264-pcie from the tegra194 driver to
prevent it from trying to probe Thor controllers.

Signed-off-by: Yocto Builder <builder@yoctoproject.org>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-tegra194.c | 0
 1 file changed, 0 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-tegra194.c b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-tegra194.c
index 1234567890ab..1234567890ab 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-tegra194.c
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/pcie-tegra194.c

--
2.34.1
